
Name of file is not significant. Even the extension does not matter much. What matters is the permissions given to the file more importantly, it should have executable persmissions.

Permissions can be viewed by ls -l <filename>

echo is a shell builtin. To see if a given command is a shell builtin "type <name of builtin>". so for eg, type echo

For if statements: -eq : equal
		   -ne : not equal
	           -lt : less than
		   -gt : greater than
		   -ge : greater than or equal to
		
